d886c13b-cd56-491f-a695-b6655fa40900.2c647735-5698-4d6c-9da7-3e63cb60f7b7.description=operator - (\=\=, \!\=, >, >\=, <, <\=) the type of threshold d886c13b-cd56-491f-a695-b6655fa40900.44d3156b-09c2-4839-b6e3-4d922de6e4af.description=Iterates through a list of values.If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.. d886c13b-cd56-491f-a695-b6655fa40900.577851e3-a152-4fb3-bfe7-3e1853840548.description=Checking number of processes, threads, and their statuses. d886c13b-cd56-491f-a695-b6655fa40900.621259e9-6628-45e2-92c0-a4f86e255176.transition.description=All processor information successfully retrieved. d886c13b-cd56-491f-a695-b6655fa40900.8768f908-9ca1-4818-8db7-f6faf534c756.transition.description=Some system processors were offline d886c13b-cd56-491f-a695-b6655fa40900.af9c55e1-bbe6-4a0c-97c2-2137dca38f1e.description=operator - (\=\=, \!\=, >, >\=, <, <\=) the type of threshold d886c13b-cd56-491f-a695-b6655fa40900.b7c94231-cfdd-4c38-8bf4-c4247e7d9f43.description=operator - (\=\=, \!\=, >, >\=, <, <\=) the type of threshold d886c13b-cd56-491f-a695-b6655fa40900.description=
Checks for any cpu errors.

inputs\:
diagnostic so far - used to chain diagnostics together, and get one report. The output of previous diagnostics, or blank.
blocked threads Threshold - maximum acceptable \# of blocked threads.
CPU Usage Threshold - Maximum acceptable % cpu usage.
host - host to check.
user - username to login to host with.
password - password for user.

Responses\:
success - Diagnostic successful.
failure - something went wrong.

flow.name: Iterative CPU Diagnostic

staticBinding.value:
Check to see if a specific process is using most of the cpu time, if so, try restarting that process.
If that does not work, you may need a faster cpu and/or multiple cpus.
Ensure WMI is running and you are using a valid username and password.
Check that all processors are online.
